# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CAREER_SERVICES_API_KEY — what is it?
# You INVENT this string yourself (e.g. openssl rand -hex 32, or any long random password).
# It is NOT from Groq/Mongo/Hugging Face. It protects your public Space: only your Next.js
# server knows it and sends header X-API-Key. Set the SAME value in NUPAL-Frontend .env.local:
# CAREER_SERVICES_API_KEY=...
# If you leave this EMPTY on HF, the API will not require X-API-Key (OK for private testing only).
CAREER_SERVICES_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CORS_ORIGINS — what is it?
# Which browser origins may call the Space URL directly. For NUPAL you usually call via
# Next.js proxy (same-origin), so * is fine. For direct browser → HF, set e.g.:
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-app.vercel.app,http://localhost:3000
CORS_ORIGINS=*
